The paper presents improved algorithms for distributed matching problems, which are typically studied in the areas of distributed computing (cs.DC), distributed systems (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), network algorithms (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on distributed algorithms suggests that cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories, followed by cs.GT due to the graph-theoretic nature of the problems. The use of linear programming and approximation algorithms also suggests cs.NI and cs.SI as possible categories.
